  "riddle": "1. Seek the performer born on February 1, 1963, known for his roles in a variety of Russian films. Who is he?\n\n2. In what year did the conference that birthed a network advocating for Asian cinema first convene?\n\n3. From the conference you learned about, what is the height above sea level at which its activities take place?\n\n4. How many cultural institutions dedicated to art and history can be found in the vicinity of the network's headquarters?\n\n5. Combine your findings from clues 3 and 4. What sum do you reach?\n\n6. A renowned festival held in Korea has become a beacon for Asian cinema. What year did it first open its doors to enthusiasts of film?\n\n7. Of the digits in the year identified in clue 6, how many are there in its binary representation?\n\n8. Seek the date when the award for the best narrative film was first bestowed — what year was it?\n\n9. Just beyond the reach of cinematic recognition, how many dining establishments lie in wait near the award's venue?\n\n10. Turn your eyes towards the television awards in the Asia-Pacific realm. What is the number of film categories recognized for submission there?\n\n11. Reflect on the figure from clue 10. What is its digital root, the single digit you would arrive at by summing the numbers iteratively?\n\n12. As you venture into the world of broadcasting companies, what rating do patrons give the Comcast Building on Google Maps?\n\n13. A broadcasting entity in Japan has woven itself into the fabric of media since its inception. What year marked the beginning of Wowow Inc.?\n\n14. Calculate: What remains when you add the year from clue 2 to the result from clue 5 and the founding year from clue 8, then apply modulo 10? \n\nNow, take that final computation using results from clues 2, 5, and 8, and distill it into a single digit.",
